snippet.textDisplay: The turning point.  San Fran's defense forgets to cover the best receiver on the other team.  Kansas CIty's QB throws up a prayer to the wide open receiver, who has to wait 3 seconds for the ball to arrive, and it is caught for a first down.  A better QB would have tossed a TD.  I think Mahomes is a great QB, but his talent had nothing to do with this play.  His receivers really make him look better than he is, in most games. Put Mahomes on the Bengals team and his success would not exist.

snippet.textDisplay:
"They're gonna talk about this forever, baby. We keep rollin. It's gonna be special."

I'm gonna be telling my grandkids this story someday. And hopefully more SB wins to come! The legend of Patrick Mahomes II is only just beginning. Just imagine what will happen when he has years of experience, wisdom, training, coaching, etc. I get the sense that he's not operating anywhere close to peak performance yet. He had one of the worst 3 and a half quarters of his entire career in the Super Bowl against the best defense in the league and still was able to reach down deep and pull it off. His mental fortitude and resilience is astounding. I still feel like I'm living in a dream world. It was really hard to focus at work this week! Can't stop thinking about this win and what it means to KC. Diehard lifelong fan.
